SUMMARY:An Evening With Uli Jon Roth *rescheduled date*
DESCRIPTION:Thursday April 23rd\, 2026\nDoors | 7:00 PM\nShow | 8:00 PM \nReserved Balcony & Mezzanine Seating | $49.65 + Fees\nReserved Riser Seating | $60.25 + Fees\nReserved Orchestra Seating | $70.50 + Fees \nThe Uli Jon Roth US tour originally planned for fall 2025 has been rescheduled to April 2026. “Sometimes destiny calls for patience… Our US Tour moves to April 2026 – with more energy\, more magic\, and more music than ever before\,” explains Uli Jon Roth.  \nAll tickets remain valid but can also be refunded at the respective points of purchase. With the new dates\, Uli Jon Roth aims to offer his US fans an even more intense concert experience. Celebrating the anniversary of SCORPIONS In Trance and Virgin Killer\, along with performing his deeply heartfelt work Pictures of Destiny.  \n+$5 on All Day of Show Purchases\nThis event is all ages – 21+ With Valid ID to Drink\nCome hungry! Snacks and light bites will be available at the canteen.\n—————————————————\nPresented by Big Fan Presents\n—————————————————\nEXPERIENCE AN UNFORGETTABLE MUSICAL AND ARTISTIC JOURNEY Legendary guitarist and composer Uli Jon Roth is set to return to North America with an extraordinary new program titled “Pictures of Destiny.“ \nThis highly anticipated tour promises to be a mesmerizing three-hour extravaganza\, including the premiere of compositions from his long-awaited Requiem for an Angel. TOUR HIGHLIGHTS Uli Jon Roth will be accompanied by a full band and a string quartet\, making for an ensemble of 10 talented musicians performing on stage. The music will be enriched by dynamic multimedia projections\, offering audiences an immersive experience at seated venues. Fans will have the opportunity to witness a stunning orchestral rendition of Roth’s groundbreaking piece Sails of Charon\, alongside several new compositions and material from his acclaimed Transcendental Sky Guitar albums.  \nThere will also be a couple of classic early Scorpions tracks\, from Uli’s Tokyo Tapes Revisited DVD\, blending a touch of nostalgia with innovative artistry. While the show will include many beloved pieces\, the spotlight will shine brightly on Roth’s latest compositions\, marking their debut in the United States. ART MEETS MUSIC As a special addition\, Roth will showcase a collection of his original oil paintings\, inspired by his music and songs\, in each venue’s foyer.  \nCritics have described his artwork as “Rembrandt meets Star Wars\,” and these visually striking works of art will be integrated into the performances to enhance the audience’s journey. A TRANSFORMATIVE EXPERIENCE Roth’s tour offers more than just a concert—it is an emotional and artistic odyssey. Through his exceptional guitar artistry and evocative paintings\, Roth invites audiences to immerse themselves in a world of profound beauty and inspiration. Don’t miss this unique opportunity to witness Uli Jon Roth’s unparalleled fusion of music and visual art. \nCheck out Uli Jon Roth here!\nWebsite | Instagram |  Facebook\n—————————————————\n*Ticket Alert*  \nTickets for Mickey’s Black Box are sold through TicketMaster\, via our website\, or in person at our Box Office. Any tickets purchased elsewhere will not be honored and we are not responsible for tickets purchased from any 3rd party sellers.  Do not google the name of the band to search for tickets.  Go to Mickeysblackbox.com ONLY. Mickeysblackbox.com will never direct you anywhere but the official TicketMaster event site. \n\nAll bags are subject are to search upon entry. Tickets are non-refundable\, save for instances in which performances are cancelled by Mickey’s Black Box. For more information about our venue or to make an ADA request\, please visit the FAQ page of our website: https://mickeysblackbox.com/faq/ or call our box office line at (717) 723 – 8463.
URL:https://mickeysblackbox.com/event/an-evening-with-uli-jon-roth/
LOCATION:Mickey’s Black Box\, 101 Rock Lititz Boulevard\, Lititz\, PA\, 17543\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mickeysblackbox.com/app/uploads/2025/06/IMG_7826-scaled-e1771481283540.jpeg
